{
  "stem": "22979.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were wondering that they needed the Jewish blood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They needed, one nurse said-- and then rumor went through the whole kommando that they need the blood for the wounded German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So even before the end of the war, not [? only ?] they squeezed out the life, inch by inch of us, but they squeezed out from every one of us the blood too.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then we got, you know, a whole piece of bread and some salami, a reward for having, you know, being blood donors.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was not donors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was done by force.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, this part-- I remember the first time I had the interview at the [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oral ?] History Project-- [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Lonna Silver-- ?] and I forgot it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I went back to her, and we made a two hour tape again about, you know, what happened later, because many thing I forgot, the blood taking from the whole kommando, 600 girls.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So it was December already, and they were losing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they still squeezed out not only the life, but the blood of us too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I'm just saying what cruelty, through the last minute, went on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Even the [? mass-- ?] whatever they could do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, you know, the hanging in January of the four girls who smuggled the gun powder.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, you know, the, the, the feeling and the scariness that now they are to end-- when it's our turn, when they are going to kill us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know how it goes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then the 18th of January, 1945, we had to line up again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the whole Auschwitz complex was evacuated, everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, Auschwitz had many side camps-- Buna, Monowitz, beside Birkenau, [NON-ENGLISH], Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
